cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO 

The paper deals with developing a system to disambiguate objects based on physical descriptions, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, such as Bayesian Eigenobjects, to learn from a small amount of labeled data and generalize to new viewpoints, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI and cs.LG. Finally, the paper demonstrates the system on a Baxter robot, which involves robotics (RO) and further supports the inclusion of cs.RO as a likely sub-category.
